  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air, then boil a kettle</p><p>Crush the <strong>cardamom pods</strong> open by squashing them with a knife</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 300ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and add the <strong>sultanas</strong> to soak</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/835.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/835.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/835.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/835.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/835.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot with a matching lid, with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and <strong>crushed</strong> <strong>cardamom pods</strong>, and cook for 20 secs until sizzling, then add the <strong>basmati rice</strong> and<strong> chicken stock</strong> and increase the heat to high</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked – this is your <strong>sultana rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/835.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/835.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/835.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/835.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/835.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and grate the <strong>carrots</strong></p><p>Trim and slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p><p>Add the <strong>grated carrot</strong>, <strong>sliced spring onion </strong>and <strong>nigella seeds</strong> to a large mixing bowl and set aside – this is your <strong>Indian-style carrot slaw</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/835.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/835.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/835.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/835.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/835.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chicken breast portions</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>curry powder</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and mix until fully coated – this is your <strong>coated chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/835.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/835.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
